This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a deep learning method for toxicity prediction. Additionally, the use of multiple neural network types and data representations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The inclusion of image data representations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of numerical features and the focus on prediction accuracy suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-category cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
